cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SY, cs.CL 

The paper discusses the implementation of symbolic computation in neural substrates, which falls under the category of neural networks and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves the simulation of automata and parsing of sentences, which could fall under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) respectively. Finally, the paper proposes a new architecture for neural networks, which could also be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning).
